#!/bin/sh
# er-example — demonstrates markdown rendering in eventrelay pages
# Format: markdown
#
# This script shows what's possible with the markdown format.
# Use it as a template for building your own dashboard pages.

cat << 'MARKDOWN'
# Dashboard Example

This page demonstrates the markdown rendering capabilities available to eventrelay page scripts.

## Text Formatting

Regular text, **bold text**, and `inline code`.

> Blockquotes work too — useful for callouts or notes.

## Lists

Unordered:
- First item
- Second item with **bold**
- Third item with `code`

Ordered:
1. Step one
2. Step two
3. Step three

## Tables

| Service | Port | Status |
|---------|------|--------|
| eventrelay | 6060 | running |
| postgres | 5432 | running |
| redis | 6379 | stopped |

## Code Blocks

```
$ eventrelay send -s demo -a hello -d '{"msg":"world"}'
sent (seq 42)
```

## Dynamic Content

Scripts can mix static markdown with dynamic output:

MARKDOWN

printf "**Current time:** %s\n\n" "$(date)"
printf "**Hostname:** %s\n\n" "$(hostname)"
printf "**User:** %s\n" "$(whoami)"
